<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">28.04.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The theoretical scope of the course forms the basis of vocational courses, professional practices and branches of science supporting this field in the field of nutrition and dietetics in the 3rd and 4th grades. The course contributes to the integration of theoretical and applied knowledge of the field and outside the field, by using the scientific literature correctly, to reach evidence-based information, to evaluate the foods that are likely to be encountered throughout life, and to make appropriate nutritional recommendations. It contributes to the acquisition of the knowledge, skills and competencies required for the planning of the nutritional care process and its implementation within the framework of ethical principles. The course will be conducted face to face. In this course, in which student-centered education is used intensively, question-answer, discussion-based learning activities, and discussion of the feedbacks of the given assignments will be included in order to facilitate the active learning component of the course.</Data></Cell>
