<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">12.11.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Functions and requirements of water and micronutrients, diseases/disorders caused by insufficient or excessive intake; It is an application-oriented course designed to provide basic information about food preparation, cooking methods and food groups, structural properties of foods, functions related to preparation and cooking, preserving their nutritional value and quality, and healthy and safe processing methods. In this course, the structural and functional properties of food and beverages from different food groups are explained, and the relationship between these properties and the preparation, cooking and processing methods in the kitchen and food industry is discussed theoretically. Some of the theoretical information is shown by applying tariffs in the laboratory environment.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=422354&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
